ATG_Ch16

- Kahneman and Tversky risk-seeking experiment in asking people about saving lives; changing the wording turns people from being risk-averse to risk-seeking. Very interesintg. The conclusion is that people exhibit 'loss-aversion'. p273
- Humans are not 'invariant' physhologically; that is it does, it does not hold that if A < B < C that they will always choose C over A. p276
- The greater the number of options, the higher the probability assigned to them. p280


